==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Mocking
<hw>Mock"ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Imitating, esp. in derision, or so
as to cause derision; mimicking; derisive.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Mocking thrush</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any
species of the genus <gen>Harporhynchus</gen>, as the brown thrush
(<spn>Harporhynchus rufus</spn>).</cd> -- <col><b>Mocking wren</b></col>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>any American wren of the genus
<gen>Thryothorus</gen>, esp. <spn>Thryothorus
Ludovicianus</spn>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mocking bird</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>mockingbird</ent>⟦br⟧
